#  db        prisma    :   Naahio
*  Game    + design    :   Asofi
*  Chat    + design    :   Toxilafa
*  Account + design    :   Penguin

    # Rules :
        -   Your website backend must be written in **NestJS**.
        -   The frontend must be written with a **TypeScript** framework of your choice.
        -   you must use the latest stable version of every library or framework used in your project.
>`-   You must use a **PostgreSQL** database.`
        -   Your website must be a **single-page application**.
        -   Everything has to be launch by a single call to: ****{ docker-compose up --build }****.
    
    # Security :
        -   password stored in your database must be hashed.
        -   website must be protected against SQL injections.
        -   must implement some kind of server-side validation for forms and any user input.
        -   any credentials, API keys, env variables etc... must be saved locally in a **.env** file.
        
    #  User Account :
        -   must login using the OAuth system of 42 intranet.
        -   user should be able to choose a unique name that will be displayed on the website.
        -   user should be able to upload an avatar.
        -   user should be able to enable two-factor authentication.
        -   user should be able to add other users as friends and see their current status.
        -   Stats have to be displayed on the user profile. (wins and losses, ladder level, achievements . . )
        -   user should have a Match History.

    #   Chat :
        -   user should be able to create channels (chat rooms) that can be either public, or private, or protected by a password.
        -   user should be able to send direct messages to other users.
        -   user should be able to block other users.
        -   user who has created a new channel is automatically set as the channel owner.
            ->  The channel owner can set a password required to access the channel.
            ->  The channel owner is a channel administrator.
            ->  The administrators of a channel can ban or mute users for a limited time.
        -   The user should be able to invite other users to play a Pong.
        -   The user should be able to access other players profiles.
    
    #   Game :
        -   users should be able to play a live Pong game versus another player directly on the website.
        -   the user can join a queue until they get automatically.
        -   must be faithful to the original Pong (1972).
        -   the user should be able to select a default version of the game without any extra features.
        -   The game must be responsive.
        -   The user should be able to watch a live play between other users.
       
